I had some trouble getting this unzipped so I'll let you in on how i did it. 
If your using winrar, you need to open the file and select it from the program list windows gives you. Once you have one file open you should see the ISO file displayed in WinRar. Just set it to extract that and it will take the pieces from all the files and make the ISO. Good luck and have fun!

The first thing is not "how can i play ps2 games in my pc?" Its "Is my computer powerful enough to run ps2 games". Pcsx2 needs an uber fast computer and a great graphics card. Cover that, and read on.

Okay. First your going to need Pcsx2. Yes, I know you already have it. Okay, First get PowerISO. Download it from Google. Okay. Now go to Google or YouTube and find out how to make a DVD image. Now insert your ps2 game and make an image. Best to save on desktop (the image, I mean). Now go to Emule and download a bios. Copy aand Paste in the Pcsx2 BIOS folder. Now Goto File=>Open image or something. and goto your desktop(or where you saved the file) And run it. Good Luck.
